HEADWORD: Efflation
<hw>Ef*fla"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of filling
with wind; a breathing or puffing out; a puff, as of wind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A soft <qex>efflation</qex> of celestial fire.</q>
<rj><qau>Parnell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Effloresce</ent>⟦br⟧
